==English==
===Interjection===
'''meh...'''
# Expressing [[indifference]] or [[apathy]].
#: ''"What do you want for dinner?" &mdash; "Meh."''
# Expresses confusion; similar to [[what the hell]].
# The verbal equivalent of a shrug of the shoulders.
#: ''"(While holding gun to their own head) Give me one good reason why I shouldn't pull this trigger!" &mdash; "Meh."'' (they HAVE to be taking the piss)
# Means anything that the user wants it to mean. For example: "Yes, No, Maybe, etc..."
# Meh means so much but nothing really.
#: ''Note: Meh is most often used to form a negative or unenthusiastic reply, even if it is meant as "''Yes''".''
# A negative comment that basically describes a dislike and distaste for something or someone, or how you feel. im not paying attention anymore because nothing i say will change anything. "how are you? meh"
